text.tspan: Information on the nature of blood donations needs to be provided
to the donor before their consent can be obtained. If the donor
does not conset, the process has to terminate.
After the blood collection, the donor should be monitored for the
duration of the bleeding. If this monitoring takes longer than 15
minutes a physician needs to asses the donor.
Whichever resource executed the preparations for the
venepuncture, should also conduct the venepuncture
The eligibility of the potential donors should be evaluated using an
interview, a questionnaire and through direct questions by a
